    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

I must confess to deep disappointment. I believed that I had accepted the possibility that the Archive had been lost to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' flames, but obviously some hope for its preservation lingered still in my breast. Perhaps you think this scholar possessed of a naivet√© unbefitting his years, but the Sages were known to be the foremost practitioners of Tharavis' sigil. If they could find any way to protect a prize of such value, they would have.

I suppose Terratus will have to endure this tragedy as it has the many that have come before.

You are always welcome in our company. 

- Fatebinder Rhogalus</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
